<HEADLINE> Montjeu Wins Arc de Triomphe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PARIS (AP) -- Montjeu won the Arc de Triomphe on Sunday,  
overtaking El Condor Pasa late in the showcase race to complete an 
exceptional season. 
</P>
<P>
	Montjeu, ridden by Mick Kinane and trained by John Hammond,  
captured the French and Irish derbies earlier this year. The 
victory in the 78th edition of the race at Longchamps was worth 
$862,000. 
</P>
<P>
	Jockey Olivier Peslier, attempting to win a fourth consecutive  
Arc de Triomphe, was well back on Borgia. 
</P>
<P>
	El Condor Pasa was trying to become the first Japanese-owned  
horse to win this race the Arc de Triomphe. He led from the start 
and was ahead by about three lengths with more than a furlong to 
go. 
</P>
<P>
	But Montjeu closed the gap and moved in front with less than a  
furlong left. He won by two-thirds of a length, covering the 1 1/2 
miles on a soft track in 2 minutes, 37 seconds. Croco Rouge was a 
distant third. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
