<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Soaring Swiftly Wins Flower Bowl </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Soaring Softly, a model of consistency since  
being switched to the turf March 1, used a powerful stretch run for 
a one-length victory in the $500,000 Flower Bowl Handicap at 
Belmont Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The win was Soaring Softly's sixth in seven career starts on the  
grass. 
</P>
<P>
	Coretta, who held a brief lead in midstretch, finished second,  
7 3/4 lengths ahead of Mossflower. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the third graded stakes win for Soaring Softly. She took  
the New York Handicap July 17 and the Sheepshead Bay May 31. 
</P>
<P>
	The 4-year-old filly was reserved toward the rear of the field  
by Jerry Bailey as Heritage of Gold set pedestrian fractions. Then, 
Bailey got Soaring Softly rolling and she wore down the leaders 
through the stretch. 
</P>
<P>
	Soaring Softly carried 118 pounds over 1 1/4 miles in 2:01 2-5 on  
the firm inner turf course and earned $300,000 for Joan G. and John 
Phillips. 
</P>
<P>
	She returned $8.10, $3.60 and $2.70. Coretta paid $4.10 and $3  
and Mossflower was $3.10 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
