<HEADLINE> Jazz Sign Forward Pete Chilcutt </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- The Utah Jazz signed forward Pete Chilcutt  
to a one-year contract Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Salary terms weren't disclosed, but he was expected to earn the  
league minimum for an 8-year veteran, $760,000. 
</P>
<P>
	Chilcutt averaged 3.6 points, 2.5 rebounds and 15 minutes per  
game in 46 games for the Vancouver Grizzlies last season. 
</P>
<P>
	In his eight-year career, Chilcutt has played in 528 games,  
averaging 4.5 points and 3.4 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Chilcutt played for the 1994-95 Houston Rockets NBA championship  
team, starting 15 of 20 games during the 1995 playoffs and 
averaging 4.5 points and 2.9 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
	Chilcutt was a first-round selection and the 27th overall pick  
by the Sacramento Kings in 1991. 
  	   	
</P>
