<HEADLINE> Spurs Sign 7-Foot Center Lindeman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN ANTONIO (AP) -- The San Antonio Spurs on Sunday signed  
7-foot, 265-pound center Todd Lindeman, who played in the CBA the 
last three seasons. 
</P>
<P>
	Lindemann averaged 8.0 points and 5.5 rebounds for the  
Connecticut Pride over 141 games the last three seasons. Terms of 
the contract were not disclosed. 
</P>
<P>
	Coach Gregg Popovich had been expected to bring another big man  
to training camp, but Ruben Garces, the player the Spurs initially 
wanted and signed last Friday, failed his physical. 
</P>
<P>
	The Spurs, the defending NBA champions, have 19 players in camp,  
13 signed to guaranteed contracts. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
