<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-03 12:40:03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits 65th Homer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Mark McGwire hit his 65th home run Sunday,  
moving past Ted Williams and Willie McCovey into 10th place on the 
career list with 522. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire connected in the first inning on a 2-2 fastball from the  
Cubs' Steve Trachsel, who allowed McGwire's record-setting 62nd 
home run last year. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire has a two-homer lead over Chicago's Sammy Sosa, who hit  
a three-run homer off Larry Luebbers in the third. 
</P>
<P>
	The drive by McGwire, estimated at 461 feet, was his fourth  
straight to straightaway center, and a kid wearing a McGwire jersey 
wound up with the ball following a scramble. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire also homered in the first inning Saturday and has two  
homers in the closing three-game series. He has six homers in the 
last seven games, reminiscent of last year, when he hit five in the 
final three to wind up with a record 70. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire saluted the Cardinals' owners box on his way to the  
dugout and then made a curtain call. He has 147 RBIs, matching the 
career high he set last year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
