<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mash One Wins Oak Tree Turf </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Mash One, ridden by David Flores, stayed  
just off the pace most of the way and rallied in the stretch Sunday 
to win the $300,000 Oak Tree Turf Championship. 
</P>
<P>
	Lazy Lode, with Gary Stevens aboard, finished second in 1 1/4-mile  
race on turf for 3-year-olds and up. Favorite Bonapartiste finished 
third, 2 1/4 lengths behind Lazy Lode. 
</P>
<P>
	All of the first three finishers carried 124 pounds. The winner  
was timed in 1:59. 
</P>
<P>
	Lazy Lode, who won Hollywood Turf Cup at Hollywood Park last  
December, has won five of his 21 starts and earned $812,325. 
Majorien has five wins in 18 races and earnings of $406,467. 
</P>
<P>
	Bonapartiste, a 5-year-old French-bred son of Kendor, finished  
second behind Military in last year's race. Bonapartiste, who has 
won six of 25 starts and earned $529,779, was ridden by Chris 
McCarron. 
</P>
<P>
	Sayarshan, ridden by Brice Blanc, came in fourth. Majorien,  
ridden by Pat Day, took fifth place. Docksider, shipped from Great 
Britain and making his United States debut, took sixth. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
