country on Sunday, the day King Letsie III had declared a national 
day of prayer for rain. Rain started falling as many people arrived 
at their churches for worship. Lesotho's early drought warning unit 
reported rain shortages in July and in August said they could 
affect winter wheat that had already been planted. 

