<HEADLINE> Kenyans Dominate Men's Races </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LIDINGO, Sweden (AP) -- Barnabas Kosgei beat two-time defending  
champion Isaac Chembobo by nearly two minutes Sunday to win the 
men's 30-kilometer race in the Lidingoloppet, the world's biggest 
cross country festival. 
</P>
<P>
	Kosgei, running the grueling 18.6-mile event for the first time,  
was timed in 1 hour, 36 minutes, 1 second. Chembobo clocked 
1:37:59. 
</P>
<P>
	Geoffrey Tanui completed the medals sweep for Kenya, finishing  
third at 1:38:01. 
</P>
<P>
	Finland's Annemarie Sandell won the women's 15K race for the  
fifth time at 54:35, nearly a minute ahead of Gunhild Halle of 
Norway. 
</P>
<P>
	More than 23,000 runners competed.  
  	   	
