<HEADLINE> Lightning Trade Daigle to Rangers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TAMPA, Fla. (AP) -- The Tampa Bay Lightning have traded former  
No. 1 draft pick Alexandre Daigle to the New York Rangers for 
future considerations. 
</P>
<P>
	Daigle, who went unclaimed in last week's waiver draft, had been  
assigned to the Lightning's AHL affiliate in Providence, R.I., on 
Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The 6-foot center, drafted first overall by the Ottawa Senators  
in 1993, had six goals and six assists in 32 games for the 
Lightning last season after his trade from Philadelphia on Jan. 29. 
</P>
<P>
	The Senators had high hopes for Daigle, giving him a  
$12.5-million, five-year deal at the age of 18. He played parts of 
five seasons with the Senators before his trade to Philadelphia. 
</P>
<P>
	He made the jump to the NHL directly from his junior club, but  
did not live up to expectations. His best season was 1996-97, when 
he scored 26 goals for the Senators. 
</P>
<P>
	The 24-year-old from Montreal is scheduled to earn $1 million  
this season. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
