<HEADLINE> Possible Mets, Reds Game Delayed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The one-game playoff between Reds and New York  
Mets will be played at 7:05 p.m. EDT Monday night at Cincinnati's 
Cinergy Field, five hours later than originally scheduled. 
</P>
<P>
	The National League made the switch at about 11 p.m. EDT Sunday  
night because the Reds' game at Milwaukee started at 9:52 p.m EDT 
after a rain delay of 5 hours, 47 minutes. Cincinnati's 7-1 win, 
which forced the playoff, didn't end untul after 12:30 a.m. EDT 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Cincinnati and New York are each 96-66. If Cincinnati is the  
wild card, the Reds would open the first round of the postseason at 
Atlanta and Houston would open at Arizona. 
</P>
<P>
	If the Mets are the wild card, they would open the postseason at  
Arizona and the Astros would open at Atlanta. Teams from the same 
division cannot meet in the first round. 
</P>
<P>
	In the last one-game playoff, the Chicago Cubs beat the San  
Francisco Giants 5-3 to win last year's NL wild card. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
