<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Weather Postpones NHRA Eliminations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOPEKA, Kan. (AP) -- Sunday's cold weather forced officials to  
postpone competition during eliminations at the Advance Auto Parts 
NHRA Nationals at Heartland Park Topeka. 
</P>
<P>
	The race is the 18th of 22 events in the $40 million NHRA  
Winston Drag Racing Series. 
</P>
<P>
	Eddie Hill, the No. 1 qualifier, pedaled his Top Fuel Dragster  
past David Gubnic to advance to the quarterfinals. Doug Herbert, 
Doug Kalitta, Tony Schumacher, Gary Scelzi, Mike Dunn, Joe Amato, 
and Kenny Bernstein all advanced past the first round as well. 
</P>
<P>
	Funny Car driver Whit Bazemore defended his No. 1 qualifying  
position by defeating Larry Huff in the first round. Frank 
Pedregon, Cristen Powell, Tommy Johnson Jr., Tony Pedregon, Jim 
Epler, Del Worsham and John Force all moved into the quarterfinals 
with first-round wins. 
</P>
<P>
	In a major upset, Mike Edwards used a hole shot to defeat No. 1  
qualifier Richie Stevens. Ron Krisher, Mike Trumble, Jeg Coughlin, 
Warren Johnson, Kurt Johnson, Troy Coughlin and Steve Schmidt will 
all race in the second round. 
</P>
<P>
	Bob Panella took over the NHRA Winston Pro Stock Truck points  
lead defeating Chip Ippolito and Kim Smith in the first two rounds 
of eliminations. Pro Stock Truck drivers Scott Perin, Mike Coughlin 
and Larry Kopp will join Panella in the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
	The professional eliminations were re-scheduled for Monday  
morning. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
