<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> One Killed in Colorado Explosion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OLATHE, Colo. (AP) -- An explosion and fire Sunday at a western  
Colorado construction-materials plant killed one worker and injured 
another, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
	A small fire broke out near the paint room at the  
Louisiana-Pacific plant at about 1:30 p.m., the Montrose County 
Sheriff's Office said. 
</P>
<P>
	The fire was put out and employees continued working, but there  
was an explosion in the same area forty minutes later that caused a 
larger blaze, the sheriff's office said. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities identified the worker who was killed as Gary  
Thornton, 53. His body was found near the area where the blast took 
place. The cause of death had not been determined. 
</P>
<P>
	A 43-year-old worker was taken to Delta County Memorial  
Hospital, where an official said he was being treated for smoke 
inhalation and was in stable condition. 
</P>
<P>
	There was extensive damage to the plant.  
</P>
<P>
	Olathe is about 210 miles west of Denver.  




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
